      skos:note "The 'How to hold it' section uses imperative voice throughout: 'Pre-register the comparison before building,' 'Keep the baseline as a real control,' 'Report the actual numbers,' 'If a metric falls short, iterate — don't narrate around it.' Authoritative, directive register with no hedging." ;
