      skos:note "The phrase 'aswritten is its own first user' is a rhetorical anchor that grounds the eval discipline in product identity rather than process compliance. It elevates the principle from a rule to a founding thesis. Consistent with the idiolect pattern of grounding operational decisions in product philosophy." ;
